description.narrative: (Bangladesh): .The NGO Health Service Delivery Project (NHSDP) provides high quality primary health care services to Bangladesh's poor through a nationwide network of 388 clinics. The network of clinics serves a population of 24 million people, and emphasizes services for women and children under five. USAID Bangladesh will use FY 2016 funds to promote increased use of health facilities by the poor as well as strengthened capacity by health facility to provide services for maternal, neonatal, child health, nutrition, family planning, and to a lesser extent tuberculosis. The clinics are managed by sub-grants to 25 non-government organizations (NGOs). USAID will continue to provide grants to the NGOs to enable them to continue to strengthen and improve their NGO and clinic management practices, continue to increase equity in access to health services, and improve quality of health services....
